pleted, ship:failed","createdAt":"2026-04-10T16:17:53.227Z","wordCount":963,"positions":[0,7,14,21,29,34,50,59,68,85,94,108,115,122,134,144,148,153,160,166,173,181,189,197,205,210,221,234,247,254,260,270,278,288,297,307,321,329,344,359,366,374,383,397,408,419,424,438,454,468,479,486,498,505,509,515,522,528,533,544,549,557,563,571,582,588,595,601,611,623,635,647,654,662,668,677,686,689,697,702,709,716,721,729,736,747,753,760,764,769,778,785,791,798,804,807,813,820,827,834,842,850,861,866,877,883,894,901,912,919,930,937,941,952,957]},"ep_stage_diary_001":{"taskId":"2291-260417-184347","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_001","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"build\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Chore tasks can still have meaningful build verification — the build stage here confirmed decompose creates worktrees and triggers parallel builds even when source files pre-exist.\",\"scope\":\"pipeline\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"The decompose pipeline requires complexity_score >= 4 and decomposable: true to trigger sub-task splitting; these thresholds are enforced in status.json.\",\"scope\":\"kody\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Decompose expects 2+ sub-tasks, parallel builds, and a PR body with a 'Decomposed Implementation' section as part of its verification contract.\",\"scope\":\"kody\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Without prior decompose runs, globbing for decompose log files in the task directory will return nothing — logs only appear after decompose executes.\",\"scope\":\"kody\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T18:57:18.003Z","wordCount":839,"positions":[2,10,18,31,38,47,54,60,70,81,92,98,117,123,129,134,144,154,162,176,185,194,201,211,218,224,228,237,245,258,265,278,289,299,308,317,328,343,357,365,373,377,382,399,414,426,433,441,449,458,465,478,485,495,506,510,517,526,540,543,556,567,583,594,606,619,631,639,648,655,664,671,679,685,695,701,714,724,728,741,746,761,768,778,783,788,795,801,811,823,831]},"ep_stage_diary_002":{"taskId":"2291-260417-184347","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_002","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"React hooks (useCallback, useEffect, etc.) cannot be placed after an early-return guard; move all hook calls before any conditional return to satisfy react-hooks/rules-of-hooks.\",\"scope\":\"src/components/notifications/toast.tsx\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Files produced by @kody decompose introduce lint errors (unused imports, missing return types, barrel re-exports) that must be fixed before pipeline merge — generated code is not lint-clean by default\",\"scope\":\"@kody decompose pipeline\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When a component has an early no-op return, all useCallback/useEffect calls must precede it even if they appear logically unnecessary — the call site, not the function body, determines the rule violat\",\"scope\":\"React Hooks\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T18:59:26.851Z","wordCount":798,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,61,68,81,92,98,108,115,124,130,137,144,153,158,164,171,175,187,197,205,211,217,226,235,243,247,258,272,278,286,293,302,309,315,328,333,343,353,358,366,373,382,390,397,404,411,414,428,436,442,449,458,466,476,484,488,493,502,512,521,526,536,549,556,565,579,596,602,605,608,620,632,642,648,653,664,677,684,694,712,717,723,731,740,746,761,766,775,783,789]},"ep_stage_diary_003":{"taskId":"2291-260417-184347","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_003","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"@kody decompose can introduce lint errors into the codebase — always run lint/verify after a decompose run to catch issues before merge.\",\"scope\":\"pipeline\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Conditional useCallback calls inside early returns violate React hooks rules and must be restructured so hooks are called unconditionally at the top level.\",\"scope\":\"React hooks\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"When fix-lint runs on a stage with known lint failures, fix those errors in the same stage rather than surfacing them for a later pass.\",\"scope\":\"pipeline\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T19:15:35.063Z","wordCount":609,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,52,60,65,79,89,94,101,110,121,128,132,137,144,152,162,169,175,182,189,198,206,219,226,235,242,254,266,272,279,285,293,301,307,313,323,331,344,347,357,364,387,391,400,408,414,424,431,444,456,460,465,475,486,492,497,507,517,531,536,542,549,554,575,581,589,597]},"ep_stage_diary_004":{"taskId":"2291-260417-184347","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_004","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"payload.find({limit:0}) discards results; markAllRead was counting the query result (always 0), not actual matching rows.\",\"scope\":\"src/services/notifications.ts:42-50\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Dynamic $and/$or operators in payload.find() create SQL injection surface even with the ORM; prefer explicit typed queries over raw object merging.\",\"scope\":\"src/services/notifications.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Pipeline verification tasks generate artifacts (event logs, stage diaries, graph nodes) that get committed alongside any real changes — review must separate signal from noise.\",\"scope\":\"pipeline/kody\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"The task decomposition verification succeeded: @kody decompose correctly split the composite notification-system task into parallel sub-tasks covering models, services, routes, utils, and tests.\",\"scope\":\"pipeline/kody\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Review stage should produce a verdict (PASS/FAIL), summa","createdAt":"2026-04-17T19:17:03.645Z","wordCount":1000,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,63,69,79,88,97,113,126,132,140,151,155,162,171,179,187,191,200,214,217,220,227,234,243,250,267,280,288,295,302,306,316,324,338,343,350,359,365,373,378,382,389,400,408,412,421,435,442,449,458,465,474,487,493,502,513,519,525,531,540,546,55